item.dc:creator: @Fridder Fridder
item.description:
@Fridder wrote:

[quote=“runescape sucks, post:10, topic:467191”][quote author=Camballer link=topic=584125.msg4155978#msg4155978 date=1352687233]
Simple, go into where you made yourself owner in the first place, make a new account with owner rights, ::unipban (your name). DONE
[/quote]
Can’t tell if trolling, or just stupid.

He’s IP banned, meaning he can no longer log in from that IP.[/quote]

Logging in with ‘localhost’ is different from logging in from ‘192.168..**’, and these are all different from logging in from your actual IP. There are 3 different IP addresses you can use to connect from (if you are hosting the server).

item.title: Iped myself from my zenith server
item.dc:creator: @Fridder Fridder
item.description:
@Fridder wrote:

Host Gushers:

Search ur name in source and client to be exact

Why would you search your username in the first place? Why would you even look in the CLIENT? IP bans are saved in IP address format… It’s not going to have his username in there. If ‘Zenith’ is a higher-revision server (or a well-programmed other server like that 474 canownyoueasy released a while back), the IP bans are saved in a different format (I believe .dat) and a person can’t read it.

OP you can look at where the bans are being read and processed from and find that file and modify it (if it’s in a text format). Otherwise you can probably make a command to remove your IP from the .dat without corrupting the file.

Read full topic
